<br>
To do zone in mobs, one group or 3-4 hardcore people. I've heard of people duoing the bottom floor but you'd have to be very well geared and I don't think your kill rate would be high enough for effective spell farming.<br>
<br>
To do the Rhag's, well that depends on your guilds power level and equipment. We've killed the Rhag's with three non-optimized groups, one could do it with less. 4 groups from any semi-decent low level raid guild would cream them, they're not as tough as Vindi but they do flurry a heck of a lot so you'll need a well decked warrior.<br>
<br>
Not sure on levels, almost everyone in my guild is 60 but I'd say that L55+ is a good starting point for this zone. Hopefully your main tank is fielding at least 5k HP otherwise he's going to have a nasty time. Even the zone in mobs hit REAL hard.<br>
<br>
Rhag 1 is slowable, can't remember if Rhag 2 is slowable or not but I THINK he is. Both of them are perma-rooted so stand back and debuff then charge.<br>
<br>
Rhags are nice because they are pretty close, not too hard and drop plenty of spells. Trouble is this also means on most servers they breathe air for about 20 mins before they die each time they pop.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=http://www.afflictionguild.com/profile.php?username=Zaniel&charactername=Zaniel>Zaniel Stormseeker</a><br><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>60th Arch Mage</a><br><a href=http://www.afflictionguild.com>Affliction</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucydmab.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cydmab</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 400<br> <font color=#333333>(4/8/02 2:07:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=364.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Power/size needed to reach spell mobs in Ssra Temple</span><hr size=1> One important thing: patrollers and guards don't drop spells. You have to move in a bit from the zone in. I'd recomend 4 hard core level 60s or a full balanced party 57+ or a small raid of 49-56. 2 people could do the zone in stuff, but 2 people doing an elite guard or a commander (which can spawn out of any spell dropping mob)... that would be impressive.<br>
<br>
The trick to the rhag is getting there in time. The first Rhag is one of the easier sources of level 60 spells, so he tends to live about 45 minutes on my server.  <p>Master Cydmab Promethean, Triune <BR>
